name: Nandini Venkatesh
what_i_do: I major in Computer Science and Economics at the University of Maryland, College Park MD. My academic interests include cybersecurity, data analytics, and Machine Learning. I currently live in New Jersey!

pasionate: I'm very passionate about giving back to my community, which I have been able to do through teaching and working on projects pertaining to this. I have been involved in the teaching community for six years, and am still continuing to teach through my involvement on campus. I have also worked extensively on a website, Tempus, with my team that helps anyone assess their mental health through a daily tracker as well as connect with therapists and others across the globe.
hobbies: My hobbies mainly include anything related to music! I have had vocal training Indian Classical music for more than eleven years, and have also been playing several instruments for some years including violin and piano! I enjoy listening to music and learning more about music in different cultures (right now I love kpop!).
